and CCS units alone.

381
00:20:33,670 --> 00:20:35,200
Natural gas units
can only operate

382
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,860
for a small fraction
of the year,

383
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:40,240
so you must construct additional
storage and renewable generation

384
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:43,790
in order to meet the demand.

385
00:20:43,790 --> 00:20:46,280
And this is a very expensive
way of going about things.

386
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:48,160
And that creates an
opportunity for fusion

387
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:50,020
as a clean,
dispatchable resource

388
00:20:50,020 --> 00:20:52,010
to operate in a variable manner.

389
00:20:52,010 --> 00:20:53,760
And so even though
it's expensive,

390
00:20:53,760 --> 00:20:56,930
it has an important role to play
in replacing those underutilized

391
00:20:56,930 --> 00:20:58,550
alternative resources.

392
00:20:58,550 --> 00:21:00,650
Operating with this low
of a capacity factor

393
00:21:00,650 --> 00:21:03,230
also reduces the maintenance
costs of the fusion plant

394
00:21:03,230 --> 00:21:06,170
by reducing the rate at which
radiation-facing components can

395
00:21:06,170 --> 00:21:07,640
be replaced.

396
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:10,650
Next slide, please.

